 development plans for 2018 - 2022 actions that fisheries are a focus. Even more, plans reinforce county appreciation for the ocean, and they emphasize interest in developing the sector in a sustainable way. Despite movement toward ocean-based support, it is clear that Kenyan coastal counties have Economy 9 Blue entrepreneurship scoping study in Kenya yet to capitalize on the boundless potential of their access to this Blue natural resource. Furthermore, Kenya\u2019s coastline is home to both intensely crowded areas (Mombasa\u2019s population density is 67x32 the national av- erage) and notably rural areas (Tana River\u2019s population density is 1/1033 the national av- erage). With an array of settings, economic makeups, and community needs, it becomes critical to focus on enterprise solutions that speak to the diverse local contexts and area issues. Not only will this research aim to parse out how different communities expe- rience Blue Entrepreneurship growth, that is, understanding the needs of both the pro- ducing and consuming parties, but we will also consider the various ways communities are able to leverage natural resources sus- tainably, given local resource management constraints. Additionally, the Blue Economy is growing unevenly across regions and sec- tors, with supporting infrastructure follow- ing a similar pattern. Therefore, problems in an urban coastal region will not be the same as the problems in a rural one, underscoring the need for thoughtful analysis and flexible solutions. 32 Calculated from: KNBS 2019 census (see footnote #25 for citation) 33 Calculated from: KNBS 2019 census (see footnote #25 for citation) 34 National Geographic. (n.d.). Ocean. In National Geographic Education Resource Library. Retrieved 25 Feb 2021, from: https:// www.nationalgeographic.org/encyclopedia/ocean/ 35 National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA). (n.d.). How much oxygen comes from the ocean? National Ocean Service.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_ch