ably, given local resource management constraints. Additionally, the Blue Economy is growing unevenly across regions and sec- tors, with supporting infrastructure follow- ing a similar pattern. Therefore, problems in an urban coastal region will not be the same as the problems in a rural one, underscoring the need for thoughtful analysis and flexible solutions. 32 Calculated from: KNBS 2019 census (see footnote #25 for citation) 33 Calculated from: KNBS 2019 census (see footnote #25 for citation) 34 National Geographic. (n.d.). Ocean. In National Geographic Education Resource Library. Retrieved 25 Feb 2021, from: https:// www.nationalgeographic.org/encyclopedia/ocean/ 35 National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA). (n.d.). How much oxygen comes from the ocean? National Ocean Service.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a8942f4c-b6c3-46ab-9261-fd218551d84f": {"__data__": {"id_": "a8942f4c-b6c3-46ab-9261-fd218551d84f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/deep-sea-atlas-eastern-mediterranean", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Deep-sea Atlas of the Eastern Mediterranean", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/deep-sea-atlas-eastern-mediterranean", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "5c8cc570396d9141598061f72b2149df00c0020789fb5ea422c63fb345fb92c6"}, "2": {"node_id": "f5a752a8-233a-411e-abb3-ccc47c97faa6", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/